# Pre-push and pre-PR checks (match `.github/workflows/ci.yml`)

Before **`git push`** that will update a PR, or before **`gh pr create`**, run these from the repository root with dev dependencies installed (`pip install -e ".[dev]"`). Fix all failures before pushing.

## Required commands

These mirror the **CI** workflow jobs **lint** and **mypy** (Python 3.11 project):

```bash
ruff check .
ruff format --check .
mypy apps packages
```

- If `ruff format --check` fails, apply formatting with `ruff format .` (or format only touched paths), then re-run the checks.
- **`mypy`** scope is exactly `apps packages` (not `tests/` unless CI changes).

## Security (match `.github/workflows/security.yml`)

When you change application code or dependencies, also run from the repo root (with `pip install -e ".[dev]"`):

```bash
pip-audit
bandit -r apps packages alembic -c pyproject.toml -ll
```

Ruff’s **S** (bandit-style) rules are part of the default **lint** job; fixing `ruff check` covers many of the same patterns.

## Tests (recommended before PR)

When CI-relevant Python paths changed, run **`pytest`** locally. CI uses Postgres + migrations; align with `ci.yml` **test** job when possible (`alembic upgrade head` then `pytest`).

## Do not skip

Do not open or update a PR relying only on “should pass in CI”—execute **ruff** and **mypy** (andtests when practical) and resolve errors first.
